Executive Profile
Thomas W. Hill B.A., MBAChief Executive Officer, President and Director, Summit Materials, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 11 different industries.See Board Relationships61$9,924,390As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Thomas W. Hill, also known as Tom, B.A., MBA has been the Chief Executive Officer and President of Summit Materials, Inc. since September 2014. Mr. Hill founded Summit Materials, LLC in September 2009 and has been its Chief Executive Officer since September 2009. Mr. Hill serves as the President of Summit Materials Holdings II, LLC. From July 2007 to July 31, 2008, he served as the Chief Executive Officer of Oldcastle, Inc., the North American arm of CRH plc, one ... of the world’s leading construction materials companies. Mr. Hill served with CRH/Oldcastle for 28 years. He started his career in 1980 with CRH as a Financial Analyst with Amcor in Ogden, Utah. He served as Vice President and General Manager of Westile in Katy Texas since 1982 and Vice President of Development at Oldcastle since 1986. He joined CRH in 1980. Mr. Hill served as the Chief Executive Officer of Oldcastle Materials, Inc. since January 2000 and its President from 1991 to July 31, 2008. Mr. Hill served as the Chief Executive Officer at Oldcastle Precast, Inc. He served as Head at Oldcastle Products & Distribution Group. He served as Chairman of the Board of Directors of Summit Materials, LLC. He serves as a Director of Summit Materials, LLC, Continental Cement Company, LLC and EnerCrest, Inc. He has been a Director of Summit Materials, Inc. since August 2009. He served as a Director of Astec Industries, Inc. from July 2008 to August 2009. He served as a Director of CRH plc from January 1, 2002 to June 25, 2008. He served as an Executive Director of Summit Materials Holdings L.P. Mr. Hill serves as Treasurer of both the National Asphalt Pavement Association and the National Stone Association and he remains active with ARTBA’s Executive Committee. Mr. Hill served as Chairman of the American Road and Transportation Builders Association (“ARTBA”) from 2002 to 2004. He is Vice-Chairman of Highway Reauthorization task force at ARTBA. He received his MBA from Trinity College in Dublin, Ireland in 1980. He received a Bachelor of Arts in Economics and History from Duke University in 1978.Read Full Background




